      <memberdef kind="function" id="class_fw_upd_ctrl_1acbfb668d7b4cfa39aa1a5a5dac3c0e7e" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void task</definition>
        <argsstring>(void)</argsstring>
        <name>task</name>
        <reimplements refid="class_task_1a1951102653a5e603f2131b33d7636232">task</reimplements>
        <param>
          <type>void</type>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Firmware update control task function. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para>The function directly enters the endless loop and wait for messages. Task wakes up when a message is in the mailbox and read the message by calling mailbox read method which returns the pointer pElem to the message. All expected messages will be handled, in case of an unexpected message an error debug message will be triggered. Finally the message will be released by calling class <ref refid="class_pool_elem" kindref="compound">PoolElem</ref> method free, if the pointer pElem is not explicitly set to 0. <linebreak/>
 <linebreak/>
 <bold>Message Handling:</bold> <linebreak/>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>eTimerExpired: The pointer pElem will be set to 0, to prevent releasing the message because it is allocated static. Afterwards handle_timer_exp method of the state machine instance is called.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>eOtaStart: Method handle_OtaStart of the state machine instance is called.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>eFwInfo: Method handle_FwInfo of the state machine instance is called.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>eFwDlSuccess: Method handle_DlComplete of the state machine instance is called.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>eFwDlFailed: Method handle_DlFailed of the state machine instance is called. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
