        <name>startRetryTimer</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Function to start one-shot retry timer. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para>The function checks the retry counter, if it is the first retry timeout value is set to initial retry interval, otherwise current retry timeout will be multipied by 2. If current retry timeout is higher than maximum retry interval it will be limited to maximum retry interval. Finally the one-shot retry timer will be started with a duration of current retry timeout and the retry counter will be incremented by one. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
