    <briefdescription>
<para>Firmware update control task class derived from task base class. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Detailed Description </title><para>The firmware update control task implements the logic for handling OTA commands and firmware update confirmation or rejection. Furthermore it manages the retry mechanism for firmware downloads in case of an error. The class provides a Finite State Machine (FSM) for coordinating different stages of the update process, a timer used for delay reboot and download retry interval and functions to start the timer for the different purposes. It provides a function to request a download retry and functions to send JSON strings to the MQTT broker for confirmation and rejection.<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Receive<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Timer interrupt callback</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Firmware update control task (self)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Firmware update task</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>MQTT connector task</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Transmit<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Firmware update task</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>MQTT connector task</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><ref refid="struct_adxl37x" kindref="compound">Adxl37x</ref> task</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Firmware update control task (self, transmission in timer callback) </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
